data.text:
Britt Ekland (b. 1942) is a Swedish actress who started film and TV acting in Europe in the 1960s before achieving popularity as a sex symbol in America in the 1970s. A year after appearing as Soviet agent Katrina Volana in 1973's Wine, Women and War telefilm, she co-starred with Roger Moore in the James Bond film The Man with the Golden Gun, after which she continued to work in film and TV on both sides of the Atlantic into the 2000s.

Musical sidenote: Britt's voice can be heard on Rod Stewart's 1976 Number One hit, " Tonight's the Night (Gonna Be Alright)". She is the sexy, french-cooing female voice at the end, into the fadeout.Stewart and Eklund were romanticaly involved for some time.
